HEADWORD: Disprince
<hw>Dis*prince"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To make unlike
a prince.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For I was drench'd with ooze, and torn with briers, . . . ⟦br⟧
And, all one rag, <qex>disprinced</qex> from head to heel.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disprison</ent>⟦br⟧
